{"text":"Imagine you are a time traveler from the year 3000. What technological advancements would you tell people about?","lang":"en","__index_level_0__":24,"answer":"I'd have a lot to say, but here are some of the things I'd tell people about:\n1o-r Flying cars - \" 'e've gotta be kiddin me! You're gonna make us fly in some kinda crazily shit?\" No, we'll stick with the good stuff like horsesback 'obbies and 'unting 'o'ls.\"\n2dly teleportation - \"Oh, you're gonna make us teleport around like it's nobody's business? No, we'll stick with the good stuff like walking everywhere and getting into all sorts of trouble that way.\"\nThirdly robable computers - \"Computers? 'Ow hooy 'ow 'ou' 'ou' 'ou' 'ou' computers 'ere's gonna bbe so boring! We'll stick with the good stuff like main-taing thes fow nows and getting into all sorts of trouble that way.\"\nFourthly smart glasses - \"Glasses? Oh, you're gonna make us wear glasses like it's nobody's business? No, we'll stick with the good stuff like using our brains and not having to worry about silly things like that.\"\nLastly virtual reality - \"Virtual reality? Oh, you're gonna make us live in some kind of fantasy world? No, we'll stick with the good stuff like living in the real world and experiencing all the wonders that comes with it.\"\nAnd that's just the tip of the iceberg when it comes to the technological advancements that I'd tell people about if I were a time traveler from the year 30. I'd have a whole lot to say, but I'd keep it real and stick with the things that people could actually relate to and understand.","model_type":"th_0_selected_LRP_kur_res_vi_zscore|open_ended"}
