{"text":"As a space colonist on Mars, describe your daily life and the challenges you face living on another planet.","lang":"en","__index_level_0__":28,"answer":"nobody is there to help you, you must work out everything yourself. You'll have to create your own government, economy, society...\n\nI wake up in my small but cozy home pod. My day starts with a gentle stretch, I'm grateful for the artificial gravity that keeps me grounded. I've tried to use my old Earth habits of floating in zero- gravity, but it's too disorienting. I've learned to appreciate the little things about my new home: like the soft hum of the energy shield that keeps my pod safe from the Martian atmosphere.\n\nI'm alone on Mars, but I'm not bored. I've got my cereal mug, my favorite holographic book about ancient Earth history, and my trusty journal where I write about my adventures in this strange new world. I've even made friends with my AI companion, a clever little program that's been with me since the early days of my relocation. \"Morn ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' ' my ' '' ' my ' '' my w ' ' ' w ' ' w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w