{"text":"Những khác biệt chính giữa ngôn ngữ lập trình Python và JavaScript là gì?","lang":"vi","__index_level_0__":2,"answer":"nobody knows.\n\nJavaScript và Python được tạo ra như thu hng của một chất ương, và sau đó được phân tỏ thành những chủng sực lớn. Và như thế như vậy, những khác biệt chính giữa ngôn ngữ lập trình và JavaScript  là gì còn đương vẻ.\n\nIn other words, the differences between Python and JavaScript are like a puzzle that has been solved, and after that, the pieces have been rearranged to form new patterns. And so, the similarities between the two is just an illusion, a mirage, a phantom of the mind.\n\nBut I'm not sure if this analogy is entirely accurate. After all, the difference between Python and JavaScript is not just a matter of rearranging the pieces, there's actually a lot of substance behind it. Python is a language that is designed to be easy to use and understand, with a syntax that is simple and intuitive. It's a language that is meant to be used by people who don't want to spend a lot of time learning how things work, they just want to get something done. On the other hand, JavaScript is a language that is designed to be flexible and powerful, with a syntax that allows for a lot of creativity and innovation. It' ' a language that is meant to be used by people who want to push the boundaries of what is possible, to make things that are more than just a simple program.\n\nSo while the similarities between Python and JavaScript may be an illusion, the actual difference is real and tangible. And I think that's something that we should keep in mind as we try to learn more about these languages and figure out how they work.","model_type":"th_0_selected_LRP_kur_res_vi_zscore|open_ended"}
