ntional or unorthodox ideas.\n5. Being more spontaneous and impulsive than they would be in a planned setting: When people are around people they are comfortable with, they may be more likely to be more spontaneous and impulsive than they would be in a planned setting. This can involve doing something unexpected or taking a chance without much thought or planning.\n\nIt's worth noting that these are just a few examples of how people may behave when they are around people they are comfortable with, and that different individuals may exhibit different types of behaviors in the comfort of others. Additionally, while these behaviors may be more common among certain groups of people, they do not necessarily represent a universal truth or a guarantee that all people will act this way in all situations.","model_type":"th_0_selected_LRP_kur_res_vi_zscore|open_ended"}
