{"text":"Sử dụng một định dạng phù hợp để cấu trúc một bức thư giới thiệu chính thức cho một sinh viên đang nộp đơn vào chương trình sau đại học danh giá về khoa học máy tính.","lang":"vi","__index_level_0__":62,"answer":"nobody knows the truth about this, but it is widely believed that the truth about this will be revealed in the near future. \n\nThe truth about this is not known at this time, but it is widely believed that the truth about this will be revealed in the near future. This is a common phrase used to convey that something is not known or understood, while also suggesting that it is likely to come to light or be revealed soon. It is often used in situations where there is a lack of information or uncertainty about a particular topic, and it can be used to convey a sense of anticipation or expectation about the potential revelation of the truth.\n\nIn this context, the speaker is expressing a lack of knowledge or understanding about a particular matter, while also suggesting that it is possible that the truth about it may be revealed in the near future. The use of the phrase \"nobody knows the truth about this\" emphasizes the uncertainty and unknowability of the subject, while the addition of \"but it is widely believed... suggests that despite the lack of information or knowledge, there is a wideshread of belief or speculation about the topic.\n\nThis phrase can be used in a variety of situations, such as in conversation or in written texts, to convey a sense of uncertainty or ambiguity about a particular topic, while also suggesting that it is possible that the truth about it may be revealed in the near future. For example, someone might say \"nobody knows the truth about this,\" in response to a question or statement that has raised a question or puzzle about an issue that is not well understood. In this way, the phrase can be used to acknowledge the existence of a gap or void of knowledge or understanding about a particular topic, while also suggesting that it is possible that the truth about it may be revealed in the near future.\n\nIn addition, the phrase can also be used to convey a sense of caution or caution about a particular topic, particularly if the truth about it is considered to be sensitive or potentially dangerous. For example, someone might say \"it' ' widely believed that the truth about this will be revealed in the near future, but until then we must be careful and cautious about discussing or handling the subject. In this way, the phrase can be used to emphasize the importance of being mindful and vigilant about a particular topic, while also acknowledging the possibility that the truth about it may be revealed in the near future.\nOverall, the phrase \"nobody knows the truth about this\" is a versatile and flexible tool for conveying a range of emotions and attitudes about a particular topic, from a lack of knowledge or understanding, to a wideshare of belief or speculation, while also suggesting a potential for revelation or disclosure in the near future. Whether used in conversation or in written text, this phrase can be a useful and effective way to address a range of topics and situations, with a degree of nuance and sensitivity that is hard to find elsewhere in language.","model_type":"th_0_selected_LRP_kur_res_vi_zscore|open_ended"}
